Description: If you could time travel back to the 60's this is the guitar you would have to buy. Fortunately, you can buy this Fender® Classic Series 60s Stratocaster in Lake Placid Blue and can have the closest thing to a vintage strat! Vintage specs are the highlight of this guitar. Alder body, maple neck with rosewood fingerboard, 7.25" radius, 21 vintage style frets, and vintage style pickups. Weighs in at 7lbs 15 oz The pickups have the slightly fatter tone with good definition. The bridge pickup has a good growl. The neck is smooth and creamy with excellent clarity. The 2 and 4 have just enough quack. The C shape neck has just a little bit of meat to it but is still comfortable and easy to play. If you want a vintage sounding Strat at a price that fits all budgets stop in and check out this guitar.This one still has the plastic film cover on the back cover. there is one small ding on the back of the head stock as shown .
